<ITEM>On the Fates of Clergymen.</ITEM>
<ITEM>On modern Education.</ITEM>
<ITEM>A true and faithful Narra|tive of what pa&s;s'd in <HI>Lon|don.</HI></ITEM>
<ITEM>Journal of a modern Lady.</ITEM>
<ITEM>Country Life.</ITEM>
<ITEM>Cutting down the old Thorn at <HI>Market-hill.</HI></ITEM>
<ITEM>A Pa&s;toral Dialogue.</ITEM>
<ITEM><HI>Mary</HI> the Cook Maid's Let|ter to Dr. <HI>Sheridan.</HI></ITEM>
<ITEM>A Dialogue between Mad <HI>Mullineux</HI> and <HI>Timothy.</HI></ITEM>
<ITEM>Epitaph on <HI>Francis Ch<GAP DESC="blank" RESP="OXF" EXTENT="1+ letters">is.</HI></ITEM>
<ITEM>Soldier and Scholar.</ITEM>
